nd Human Nature’ and Professor D.I. McKenzie in ‘The Staple of News and the Late Plays’ offer critical assessment of plays, the one wide-ranging, the other closely focused on a previously neglected play; and Professor H.N. Maclean in ‘";A More Secret Cause”: The Wit of Jonson’s Poetry’ and Professor L.C. Knights in ‘Ben Jonson: Public Attitudes and Social Poetry’ approach the difficult and rewarding task of defining Jonson’s poetry of appraisal in different but complementary styles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aBarish, Jonas A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlissett, William, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHibbard, G.R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnights, L.C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeech, Clifford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaclean, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMckenzie, D.F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPatrick, Julian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVan Fossen, R.W., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144263216540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442632165423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442632165.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_S